('7572', '1', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat (350 to 400).'),
('7572', '2', 'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('7572', '3', 'Add onion, and cook, stirring occasionally, 5 to 7 minutes or until tender and lightly browned.'),
('7572', '4', 'Add tomatoes and olives, and cook, stirring, 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture is well blended and tomato juice has reduced slightly.'),
('7572', '5', 'Remove from heat, and stir in thyme and 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('7572', '6', 'Sprinkle tuna steaks with salt and pepper. Grill on greased grill racks 2 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7572', '7', 'Transfer tuna steaks to individual plates, and top evenly with tomato-olive mixture.'),
('7574', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients. set aside.'),
('7574', '2', 'Combine chili powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Rub tuna with chili powder mixture. coat with cooking spray.'),
('7574', '3', 'Place a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. add tuna. Cook 3 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7574', '4', 'Serve with sour cream mixture.'),
('7575', '1', 'Preheat oven to 200F. Using knife, make 9 slits in sides of tuna. Fill each with 1 clove, 1 coriander seed, and 1 garlic sliver. sprinkle tuna with salt and pepper.'),
('7575', '2', 'Heat oil in ovenproof pot over medium heat.'),
('7575', '3', 'Add onion and saute 8 minutes. push to side of pot.'),
('7575', '4', 'Add tuna and saute until brown on all sides, about 12 minutes. Scatter tomatoes, oregano, and remaining garlic slivers around tuna. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('7575', '5', 'Pour vinegar over fish.'),
('7575', '6', 'Bake tuna uncovered until thermometer inserted into center registers 145F for medium-rare, about 12 minutes.'),
('7575', '7', 'Transfer tuna to platter. Spoon tomato sauce over. Cool to room temperature. Slice tuna thinly and serve.'),
('7576', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat the broiler.'),
('7576', '2', 'In a saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('7576', '3', 'Add the onion and cook over low heat until softened but not browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('7576', '4', 'Add the yellow peppers, potato, water and a large pinch of salt. Cover and cook until the peppers and potatoes are tender, about 12 minutes.'),
('7576', '5', 'Transfer the vegetables and their liquid to a food processor and process until roughly pureed. Scrape the sauce into a bowl, add the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7576', '6', 'Brush the tuna steaks with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill or broil for 2 minutes on each side, or until lightly charred on the outside and medium rare in the center. Spoon the sauce onto large plates and set the tuna steaks on top.'),
('7576', '7', 'Garnish with sage leaves and serve.'),
('7577', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7577', '2', 'Brush fish with soy sauce.'),
('7577', '3', 'Combine 2 teaspoons pepper and sesame seeds. sprinkle evenly over fish.'),
('7577', '4', 'Add fish to pan, and cook 2 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7577', '5', 'Combine 2 tablespoons water and next 5 ingredients (through ginger) in a small bowl.'),
('7577', '6', 'Combine slaw and onions in a large bowl.'),
('7577', '7', 'Drizzle vinegar mixture over slaw mixture. toss to coat.'),
('7577', '8', 'Serve with fish.'),
('7580', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the olive oil with the parsley, red onion, vinegar, basil, cilantro, garlic, crushed red pepper and 1/2 teaspoon of the thyme. Season this chimichurri sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('7580', '2', 'Season the tuna steaks with salt, pepper and the remaining 1 teaspoon of thyme.'),
('7580', '3', 'Heat 2 large skillets.'),
('7580', '4', 'Add 1 tablespoon of the remaining olive oil to each skillet. when it shimmers, add 2 tuna steaks to each pan. Cook over high heat until browned but rare in the center, 1 to 2 minutes per side.'),
('7580', '5', 'In a large bowl, toss the mesclun with half of the chimichurri sauce and mound it on plates. Thinly slice the tuna steaks and set on the plates. Pass the remaining chimichurri sauce at the table to dress the tuna.'),
('7581', '1', 'In a medium bowl, stir together ginger, scallions, vinegar, and sesame oil. season with salt and pepper.'),
('7582', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk the wasabi powder with the tofu, rice vinegar and 1 tablespoon each of the lemon juice and mirin. In a large bowl, toss the radishes with the mint, cilantro and sprouts.'),
('7582', '2', 'Heat a cast-iron grill pan.'),
('7582', '3', 'Brush the tuna steaks with the olive oil and season generously with salt and pepper. Grill the tuna over high heat until seared outside and medium rare within, 2 to 3 minutes per side.'),
('7582', '4', 'Transfer to a platter.'),
('7582', '5', 'Add the remaining 3 tablespoons each of lemon juice and mirin to the radishes and toss to mix. Slice the tuna steaks 1/4 inch thick and serve with the radish salad and wasabi dressing.'),
('7583', '1', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('7583', '2', 'Brush fish with oil. sprinkle with herb mixture.'),
('7583', '3', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('7583', '4', 'Add fish. cook 2 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7583', '5', 'Garnish with lemon wedges.'),
('7583', '6', 'Serve with: Nioise Salad'),
('7584', '1', 'Whisk together olive oil and next 3 ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('7584', '2', 'Coat tuna with oil mixture, and sear in hot (slightly smoking) cast-iron skillet for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes per side or until rare to medium-rare.'),
('7584', '3', 'Serve over Chickpea Artichoke Salad.'),
('7586', '1', 'To prepare rice, cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Stir in 1/4 cup onions, peanut sauce, ginger, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. keep warm.'),
('7586', '2', 'To prepare tuna, heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7586', '3', 'Combine tuna and 2 tablespoons soy sauce in a bowl, tossing gently to coat. Sprinkle tuna with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Dredge edges of tuna in sesame seeds.'),
('7586', '4', 'Add tuna to pan, and cook 3 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7586', '5', 'Serve tuna over rice.'),
('7586', '6', 'Drizzle with 1 tablespoon soy sauce. sprinkle with 2 tablespoons onions.'),
('7589', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),
('7589', '2', 'Add onion, celery, parsley and garlic. Saut until onion is tender but not brown, about 10 minutes.'),
('7589', '3', 'Add tomatoes and bay leaf. Cover and cook until sauce thickens, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Rewarm before continuing.) Discard bay leaf.'),
('7589', '4', 'Mix in torn basil. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('7589', '5', 'Sprinkle tuna with salt and pepper.'),
('7589', '6', 'Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in another heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7589', '7', 'Add tuna and cook until golden and just opaque in center, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('7589', '8', 'Transfer tuna to platter. Spoon sauce over tuna.'),
('7589', '9', 'Garnish with basil sprigs.'),
('7590', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the garlic with 3/4 teaspoon of salt. mash to a paste with the back of a small spoon. Stir in the lemon juice and mayonnaise until smooth. Gradually whisk in 1/4 cup of the olive oil in a thin stream until the aioli is emulsified. Refrigerate the aioli until serving.'),
('7590', '2', 'Bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil.'),
('7590', '3', 'Add the artichokes, cover with a lid slightly smaller than the saucepan to keep the artichokes submerged and cook until the bottoms are tender, about 15 minutes.'),
('7590', '4', 'Drain the artichokes and spread them out on a large plate to cool slightly. Pull off the tough outer leaves and cut each artichoke in half. Pat dry.'),
('7590', '5', 'In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil until shimmering.'),
('7590', '6', 'Add the artichokes and cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until golden and crisp, 4 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with the chopped parsley.'),
('7590', '7', 'Transfer the artichokes to a platter and keep warm.'),
('7590', '8', 'Heat a cast-iron grill pan or large skillet. Rub the tuna with the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill the tuna over high heat, turning once, until browned and the meat is medium rare, about 3 minutes total.'),
('7590', '9', 'Transfer the tuna to the platter and serve immediately with the aioli and lemon wedges.'),
('7593', '1', 'Preheat the broiler.  Meanwhile, toss the tuna in a bowl and break up any large hunks with a fork.'),
('7593', '2', 'Add the mayonnaise and lemon juice and mash the mayonnaise and lemon in with a fork until incorporated.'),
('7593', '3', 'Fold in the celery, chives, and parsley.  Season the tuna salad with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('7593', '4', 'Lightly toast each side of bread under the broiler.  It should only take a few seconds per side.'),
('7593', '5', 'Top two of the slices of bread with the tuna salad.'),
('7593', '6', 'Add a slice of Swiss cheese to each.  Set underneath the broiler and cook until the cheese melts but does not brown.  This should definitely take less than a minute, and probably closer to 30 seconds.  Top each with a slice of bread if you like it like that, or leave it as an open-faced sandwich and serve.'),
('7594', '1', 'To prepare ponzu, place 1/2 cup orange juice and the next 5 ingredients (through 1 1/2 chipotle chiles) in a blender, and process until smooth.'),
('7594', '2', 'To prepare salsa, combine diced cucumber, tomato, avocado, and cilantro in a small bowl.'),
('7594', '3', 'Sprinkle fish with salt.'),
('7594', '4', 'Heat a large nonstick grill pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('7594', '5', 'Add fish. cook 3 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7594', '6', 'Cut each tuna steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices. Arrange sliced tuna over rice. top with salsa, and drizzle with ponzu.'),
('7595', '1', 'Place beans in medium bowl.'),
('7595', '2', 'Add enough cold water to cover beans by 3 inches.'),
('7595', '3', 'Let stand overnight.'),
('7595', '4', 'Drain.'),
('7595', '5', 'Combine beans and stock in large saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium. cover and simmer until beans are just tender, about 1 hour.'),
('7595', '6', 'Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.'),
('7595', '7', 'Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),
('7595', '8', 'Add onion, carrot and celery and saut until almost tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('7595', '9', 'Add thyme and lemon peel and stir 1 minute.'),
('7595', '10', 'Add beans, reserved 1/2 cup cooking liquid and 2 tablespoons oil and toss until heated through, about 5 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('7595', '11', 'Remove from heat. Cover to keep warm.'),
('7595', '12', 'Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in another heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle tuna with salt and pepper.'),
('7595', '13', 'Add tuna to skillet and cook to desired doneness, about 3 minutes per side for medium.'),
('7595', '14', 'Spoon beans onto center of each of 4 plates, dividing equally among plates. Top each with tuna steak. Spoon Sun-dried Tomato Sauce over tuna steaks and serve immediately.'),
('7597', '1', 'In a small saucepan, combine the soy sauce, mirin, shallot, jalapeo, orange juice, lemon zest and juice, sugar and coriander. Simmer over moderate heat until reduced by half, about 8 minutes. Strain the sauce.'),
('7597', '2', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil until shimmering. Season the tuna with salt and pepper. Cook over high heat for 1 minute per side.'),
('7597', '3', 'Transfer the tuna to a platter and let rest for 1 minute. thickly slice and serve with the sauce.'),
('7598', '1', 'For slaw and dressing'),
('7598', '2', 'Attach grating blade to food processor. Julienne each vegetable and set aside. In another bowl, mix all dressing ingredients and add vegetables.'),
('7598', '3', 'Add cilantro and combine gently.'),
('7598', '4', 'Let rest for at least 30 minutes.For tuna'),
('7598', '5', 'Place a large nonstick pan over high heat until hot.'),
('7598', '6', 'Combine sesame seeds and wasabi in a bowl. season with salt and pepper. Coat pan with cooking spray. drizzle oil in pan. Lightly salt tuna. dredge in sesame-wasabi mixture. Reduce heat to medium and place tuna in pan. Sear until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Flip. cook 2 minutes more.'),
('7598', '7', 'Remove from heat and let rest for a few minutes. Divide slaw among 4 plates and top with tuna.Source: The Lincoln, Santa Monica, CAAttach grating blade to food processor. Julienne each vegetable and set aside. In another bowl, mix all dressing ingredients and add vegetables.'),
('7598', '8', 'Add cilantro and combine gently.'),
('7598', '9', 'Let rest for at least 30 minutes.'),
('7598', '10', 'Place a large nonstick pan over high heat until hot.'),
('7598', '11', 'Combine sesame seeds and wasabi in a bowl. season with salt and pepper. Coat pan with cooking spray. drizzle oil in pan. Lightly salt tuna. dredge in sesame-wasabi mixture. Reduce heat to medium and place tuna in pan. Sear until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Flip. cook 2 minutes more.'),
('7598', '12', 'Remove from heat and let rest for a few minutes. Divide slaw among 4 plates and top with tuna.Source: The Lincoln, Santa Monica, CA'),
('7603', '1', 'If you dont have carrot juice on hand, you can use about 3 large carrots and slice them into thick chunks.'),
('7603', '2', 'Place them into a blender with 1/4 cup of water and blend until smooth.'),
('7603', '3', 'Place pulp into a fine mesh strainer over a bowl to catch the juice. Press the blended carrot with the back of a wooden spoon to squeeze the juice from the pulp until you have 1/3 cup of juice.Using an immersion blender, add all sauce ingredients into a tall bowl but leaving out the scallion. Blend on low until miso is completely dissolved.'),
('7603', '4', 'Pour into 4 serving dishes for dipping and add the scallions equally in each dish.Pan-Seared Tuna Instructions'),
('7603', '5', 'Ingredients1/8 Cup wasabi coated sesame seeds1 pound sushi-grade yellowfin tuna2 tablespoon safflower oil1 tablespoon sesame oil'),
('7603', '6', 'Spread sesame seeds thinly over a small plate. Slice thawed tuna steak into 1 inch thick strips and press into seeds, turning to coat each side.'),
('7603', '7', 'Heat oil in a medium saute pan over medium-high heat. Gently place the tuna pieces into the hot pan and cook each side until seeds are golden, about 20 seconds per side.'),
('7603', '8', 'Remove tuna from pan and place on a paper-towel-lined plate and let rest for 1 minute, then cut each piece into 1/4-inch-thick slices.'),
('7603', '9', 'Serve with a garnish of fresh, thinly-sliced ginger, chili sauce, wasabi and the ginger-carrot dipping sauce.Related Cheap Posts'),
